ce:section.ce:para:
In this study, the hydrodynamic cavitation (HC) equipment in which the venturi tube (as shown in Fig. 1
                        ) is used as a throttling device is shown in Fig. 2
                        . The HC equipment is composed of self-priming pump (1.5 kW power, WZB-1500A, Rijin Pump Co., Ltd., Japan), venturi tube, throttle valve, flowmeter, pressure gauges (P1 and P2), cooling water system and holding tank The polypropylene (PPR) tube with internal diameter of 19 mm was used to connect the above components. The role of the self-priming pump is to provide power for the entire HC equipment to drive the fluid continuously circulates in the HC system. The thermometer and pressure gauges were installed to monitor the temperature and pressure of the fluid inside the tube, respectively, and facilitate the subsequent investigation of the effects of temperature and pressure on the prepared GQDs. The flowmeter was used to measure the flow rate and flow velocity of fluid in the tube. The throttle valve was used to control the flow rate of the bypass line, which can adjust the pressure in the main line. In addition, the cooling water system of the HC equipment was used to regulate the temperature of the fluid inside the tube.
